set_instance_library(25.10)                        set_instance_library(25.10)

Name
       set_instance_library - Binds a cell library to an instance

Syntax
       set_instance_library

        [-help]

        -library <string>

        -instance <string>

        [-early | -late]

       Binds a cell library to an instance. When specified, the software over-
       rides the default binding mechanism for a cell from the library set.

       Note:  The  set_instance_library  command cannot be used at the command
       prompt - this command can be specified in the ViewDefinition file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -early Uses the library binding for early timing analysis.

       -instance <string>
              Specifies the instance for which the library binding needs to be
              done.

       -late  Uses the library binding for late timing analysis.

       -library <string>
              Specifies the library file path.

Examples
       The following commands specify the instance for which the library bind-
       ing will be done:

              * set_instance_library -library newcell.lib -instance {i1}

              * set_instance_library -library mysil.lib -instance {i1 i2}

              * set_instance_library -library  {new.lib  mysil.lib}  -instance
                {i1} -early

              * set_instance_library  -library {mynew.lib mysil.lib} -instance
                {i1 i2} -late

Related Information
